TY  - JOUR
T1  - Trust in Typical and High-Reliability Contexts: Building and Reacting to Trust among Firefighters
AU  - Colquitt, Jason A.
AU  - LePine, Jeffery A.
AU  - Zapata, Cindy P.
AU  - Wild, R. Eric
Y1  - 2011/10/01
PY  - 2011
DA  - 2011/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2006.0241
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2006.0241
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 999
EP  - 1015
VL  - 54
IS  - 5
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We develop theory that distinguishes trust among employees in typical task contexts (marked by low levels of situational unpredictability and danger) from trust in ?high-reliability? task contexts (those marked by high levels of situational unpredictability and danger). A study of firefighters showed that trust in high-reliability task contexts was based on coworkers' integrity, whereas trust in typical task contexts was also based on benevolence and identification. Trust in high-reliability contexts predicted physical symptoms, whereas trust in typical contexts predicted withdrawal. Job demands moderated linkages with performance: trust in high-reliability task contexts was a more positive predictor of performance when unpredictable and dangerous calls were more frequent.
AB  - We develop theory that distinguishes trust among employees in typical task contexts (marked by low levels of situational unpredictability and danger) from trust in ?high-reliability? task contexts (those marked by high levels of situational unpredictability and danger). A study of firefighters showed that trust in high-reliability task contexts was based on coworkers' integrity, whereas trust in typical task contexts was also based on benevolence and identification. Trust in high-reliability contexts predicted physical symptoms, whereas trust in typical contexts predicted withdrawal. Job demands moderated linkages with performance: trust in high-reliability task contexts was a more positive predictor of performance when unpredictable and dangerous calls were more frequent.
